President Obama has nominated Kenneth Allen Polite, Jr., to serve as U.S. Attorney in the Eastern District of Louisiana. Polite is a shareholder at the law firm of Liskow & Lewis and currently heads the firm's White Collar Crime Defense Group. He previously served as an Assistant United States Attorney in the Southern District of New York and as an Associate with Skadden, Arps, Slate, Meagher & Flom LLP. Polite received his J.D. from Georgetown University Law Center and his A.B. from Harvard University. President Obama expressed confidence in Polite's ability to pursue justice and serve the people of Louisiana with distinction.